parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose critical information about the vehicle's speed, fuel level, and other vital systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The speedometer
tachometer
fuel gauge
and other gauges fail to function or provide inaccurate readings
the instrument panel screen goes blank
the gauges spike or fluctuate erratically
the cluster fails to turn on or off intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system shorts out
causing a fire in the fusebox
the starter relay fails
the battery boils over
the vehicle's lights turn off and on randomly
the windows fail to open or close
the master window switch is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The low beam headlights burn out while driving
the headlights turn off and on randomly
the low beam bulbs burn out simultaneously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The turn signal switch fails
the turn signals do not work
the turn signal light is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Inlet Check Valve Fracture
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture of the fuel tank inlet check valve can cause fuel leaks, leading to a fire hazard, and may also lead to engine stalling, loss of power, and difficulty starting the engine.
symptoms: Strong gasoline odor
fuel leaks
engine stalling
loss of power
difficulty starting the engine
fuel gauge fluctuations
and check engine light illumination.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and difficulty starting the engine, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fuel gauge fluctuations
incorrect fuel level readings
and engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose critical information about the vehicle's speed, fuel level, and engine performance, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Speedometer
tachometer
and fuel gauge malfunctions
and instrument cluster failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of headlights can cause a loss of visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights suddenly turn off while driving
sometimes accompanied by the failure of daytime running lights
brake lights
or fog lights. The failure can occur at various speeds
and the headlights may turn back on after a few minutes or when the vehicle is restarted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake lights can increase the risk of rear-end collisions, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate or flicker on and off
sometimes accompanied by the failure of other lights
such as headlights or fog lights.
